S :ta Anna sjukh. åtta mån. 35-38, förste läk. v. S:t Sigfrids sjukh. sed. 36, tf. överläk. o. sjukh :chef där und. vakans, läk. v. translated: Ewaldsson, Evald Levi, first physician, practicing doctor in Växjö, born May 8th, 1899 in N. Fågelås, Skaraborg County, son of Evald Andersson and Klara Andersson. Married to Solveig Burrau in 1930. They had three children: Frans Bertil Ewald, born in 1931, Stig Ewald, born in 1936, and Betti, born in 1941. Evald passed his high school exam in 1919, completed a bachelor’s degree in medicine in 1924 and a medical license in 1929, all in Lund. He held various positions, including assistant physician at Alingsås hospital in 1927, doctor at Hälsingborgs hospital in 1930, doctor at the psychiatric hospital in Lund in 1931, second physician at S:ta Maria hospital from 1932-1935, temporary doctor and hospital manager at S:t Oloifs hospital for six months in 1935, temporary chief physician and hospital manager at S:ta Anna hospital for eight months from 1935-1938, and first physician at S:t Sigfrids hospital from 1936. He was also a doctor at Biskopsbo mental hospital and work home in Vrigstad from 1936, and a practicing doctor in Växjö from 1937.
